modules.description: This module handles OAuth 2.0 authentication for Dropbox, providing functions to initiate authorization flows, extract authorization codes or tokens from URIs, and exchange codes for access tokens. It works with URIs and string-based codes and tokens, supporting both token and code-based OAuth 2.0 workflows. Concrete use cases include redirecting users to Dropbox for login, parsing the resulting callback URI, and obtaining access tokens for API requests.

This module offers OAuth 2.0 authentication, file metadata management, and delta-based synchronization for Dropbox integration, focusing on asynchronous operations. It handles OAuth tokens, file/folder metadata, delta entries, and path-based operations, supporting large file uploads via chunked transfers and real-time change tracking. Designed for concurrent workflows, it enables applications to stream content, manage shared folders, and synchronize state efficiently using Lwt-driven non-blocking I/O.
